obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE KAZIS ACT, 1880`
  line `A CT N O.12 OF 1880 1`
  line `[9 th July, 1880. ]`
  line `An Act for the appointment of persons to the Office of Kazi ’.`
  line `W HEREAS by the preamble to Act No. 11 of 1864 2 ( An Act to repeal the law relating to t he offices of`
  line `Hindu and Muhamma dan Law officers and to the offices of Kazi ’ - ul - Kuzaat and of Kazi ’, and to abolish`
  line `the former offices ) it was (among other things) declared that it was declared that it was inexpedient that`
  line `the appointment of the Kazi - ul - Kuzaat, or of City, Town or Pargana Kazi ’ s should be made by the`
  line `Government, and by the same Act the enactments relating to the appointment by the Government of the`
  line `said officers were repealed; and whereas by the usage of the Muhammad an community in some parts of`
  line `3 [ India ] the presence of Kazi ’ s a ppointed by the G overnment is required at the celebration of marriages`
  line `and the performance of certain other rites and ceremonies, and it is therefore expedient that the`
  line `Government should again be empowered to appoint persons to the office of Kazi; It is he reby enacted as`
  line `follows: —`
  line `1. Short title. — This Act may be called the Kazi ’ s Act, 1880;`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `Local extent. — It extends, in the first instance, only to the territories administered by the Governor of`
  line `Fort Saint George in Council. 5 [ But the Government of any other State ] may, from time to time, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, extend it to the whole or any part of the territories under its`
  line `administration. 6`
  line `2. Power to appoint Kazi ’ s for any local area. — Wherever it appears to the State Government that`
  line `any considerable number of the Muhammadans resident in any local area desire that one or more Ka ’ zi ’ s`
  line `should be appointed for such local area, the State Government may, if it thinks fit, after consulting the`
  line `principal Muhammadan residents of such local area, select one or more fit persons and appoint him or`
  line `them to be Kazi ’ s for such local area.`
  line `If any question arises whether any person has been rightly appointed Kazi ’ under this section, the`
  line `decision thereof by the State Government shall be conclusive.`
  line `The State Government may, if it thinks fit, suspend or remove any Kazi ’ appointed under this section`
  line `who is guilty of any misconduct in the execution of his office, or w ho is for a continuous period of six`
  line `months absent from the local area for which he is appointed, or leaves such local area for the purpose of`
  line `residing elsewhere, or is declared an insolvent, or desires to be discharged from the office, or who refuses`
  line `or b ecomes in the opinion of the State Government unfit, or personally incapable, to discharge the duties`
  line `of the office.`
  line `1. The Act has been extended to the Union territory of Lakshadweep by Reg. 2 of 1970, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15 - 10 - 1970)`
  line `and to the Union territory of Pondicherry by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line `2. Rep.by Act 8 of 1868.`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for “the Provinces”.`
  line `4. The words “and it shall come into force at once” omitted by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3and II Schedule.`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, f or “But the Government of any other Part A State or the Government of a`
  line `Part C State”.`
  line `6. The Act has been extended to certain places in the Bombay Presidency, West Bengal, t he U.P., t he Punjab, t he C.P. and`
  line Assam.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
