  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `3. Naib Kazi ’ s. — Any Kazi ’ appointed under this Act may appoint one or more persons as his Naib`
  line `or Naibs to act in his place in all or any of the matters appertaining to his office throughout the whole or`
  line `in any portion of the local area for which he is appointed, and may suspend o r remove any naib so`
  line appointed.
  line `When any Kazi ’ is suspended or removed under section 2, his naib or naibs (if any) shall be deemed`
  line `to be suspended or removed, as the case may be.`
  line `4. Nothing in Act to confer judicial or administrative powers; or to render the presence of`
  line `Kazi ’ s necessary; or to prevent any one acting as Kazi ’ s. — Nothing herein contained, and no`
  line `appointment m ade hereunder, shall be deemed —`
  line `( a ) to confer any judicial or administrative powers on any Kazi ’ or Naib Kazi ’ appointed`
  line `hereunder; or`
  line `( b ) to render the presence of a Kazi ’ or Naib Kazi ’ necessary at the celebration of any marriage or`
  line `the perf ormance of any rite or ceremony; or`
  line `( c ) to prev ent any person discharging any of the functions of a Kazi ’.`
  line __________
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
